name: MAGENTA
description:
"Magenta doesn’t exist because it has no wavelength; there’s no place for it on the spectrum. The only reason we see it is because our brain doesn’t like having green (magenta’s complement) between purple and red, so it substitutes a new thing." -Amelia Settembre https://medium.com/swlh/magenta-the-color-that-doesnt-exist-and-why-ec40a6348256
